ARDOR is a self-service tool that helps in test order creation and fulfillment. It supports order fulfillment from lower environments MTE (managed test) and SFT. Also, it supports order fulfillment for the orders that originate from all channels like Dotcom, POS, BBFB. ARDOR can also help with triggering test emails without creating orders, that reduces the time and efforts related to setup data and environment to test emails. 

FULFILLMENT TYPES SUPPORTED BY ARDOR? 
Answer - Order Creation: 
â€¢	Ardor supports test order creation in lower environments.
â€¢	Users can create simple plain test orders for smoke testing using voice assistance.
â€¢	Ardor currently supports order creation of all fulfillment types and combinations like STH, ISPU, DELIVERY, CURBSIDEPICKUP
Order Fulfillment:
â€¢	Ardor supports test order fulfillment for the orders created in MTE and SFT
â€¢	Ardor supports the fulfillment of the orders created through various channels Ex: Dotcom, BBFB, and Retail
â€¢	Users have an option to select the different line level statuses of an order. 
â€¢	Ardor displays the statuses of the order while the fulfillment is InProgress.

ISPU FULFILLMENT

An Instore Pickup Order AKA ISP order is the order that would be created both from online and retail store where the customer comes to pick the order from store when it is ready to be picked and Inventory may be procured from same or different store based on procurement rules and inventory availability.

A. Creating an ISPU Order:- 
A.1. SKU should have ISP setup. IS_PICKUP_ALLOWED flag should be Y in

should have ISP setup. IS_PICKUP_ALLOWED flag should be Y in yfs_item table.
A.2. ISP COXML should be modified. 
A.3. ReqShipDate value Can be current or future date.
A.4. ProcureFromNode should be blank and ShipNode should be the store where the order is placed. 


B.Steps to fulfill STH or Ship to home order? 
B.1. Order can be created from any Dotcom channel from Lower environment SFT or MTE.Now the order reaches OMS and the status will be "Created" and it will get automatically scheduled if there is sufficient inventory available. On Release, it will move to "Released" status.
B.2: Ensure that the FP request ID is generated by OMS and the same is sent to WMS. WMS will now process the FP request ID and send the fulfilment acknowledge update to OMS. The status now moves to "Order Acknowledged" and it can be verified in the OMA application.
B.3: Navigate to OMA application, search the order using order number and the order will be displayed.
B.4: Edit the order and on the left-hand side, click on 'Shipping' dropdown and choose "Confirm Warehouse Shipment".
B.5: Select the release number which you want to ship and click on 'Next' button.
B.6: Select the shipping date and select the items which you want to ship in the order.
B.7: Enter a unique tracking number and click on "Confirm Shipment". Now the status of the order moves to "Shipped".
B.8: Once the invoice agent processes the order, the status of the order will move to "Shipped and Invoiced" and the same can be verified in the OMA application.
Above steps are given for single line single quantity STH order but the process is same for multiline multiÂ­ quantity STH orders as well.
If there are any changes in URL or if the order is stuck in any of the statuses, please check with the ENV team
{# help-tern) slack channel for triages. In case of data issues (No pick, Awaiting inventory), please check with the TDM team (# help-tdm) slack channel for triages.
